Operators:
----------
       its a symbol used to perform operations on values(operands)

       1.Arithmetic Operator :
                               + , - , * , / , % , ** 

            Note : + acts like concatination(merging) with string
                   `${}`acts like concatination ---interpolation
 
            Operator Presedence:
                       ()
                       **
                       * / %
                       + -

       2.Assignment Operator/compund Assignment Operator:
                              =, +=,-=,*=,/=,&=,**=
       3.Comaprision Operator/Relational Operator
                              < ,>,<=,>=,==,===,!=,!==

                Note: ==  -->checks only values and ignores data type
                      === -->checks both value and data type
        4.Logical Operator:
                      && , || , !
        5.Conditonal Operator/Ternary Operator:
                     opernad1?operand2:operand3

                     opernad1--->condition
                     operand2--->true
                     operand3--->false
        6.type of operator:
                         used to know the data type of a literal/value
        
        7.unary operator:
                 1.increment unary operator
                        1.pre-increment:
                                         ++value
                                         first increases the values , then use
                        2.post-increment:
                                         value++
                                         first it uses the value , then increases
                 2.decrement unary operator
                        1.pre-decrement:
                                         --value
                                         first decreases the values , then use
                        2.post-decrement:
                                         value--
                                         first it uses the value , then decreases
      
